quran[17]{c,v,t}:
  86,1,"By the heaven, and the night-visitor,"
  86,2,"what do you know what the night-visitor is?"
  86,3,"It is the piercing star."
  86,4,"There is no living being but there is a protector over it.",footnotes:182662:1
  86,5,"So let man consider of what he was created.",footnotes:182663:1
  86,6,"He was created of a gushing fluid,"
  86,7,"emanating from between the loins and the ribs.",footnotes:182664:1
  86,8,"Surely He (the Creator) has the power to bring him back (to life).",footnotes:182665:1
  86,9,"On the Day when man's deepest secrets shall be put to the test",footnotes:182666:1
  86,10,"he shall have no power, and no helper."
  86,11,"By the heaven with its recurring cycle of rain,",footnotes:182667:1
  86,12,"and by the earth ever bursting with verdure,"
  86,13,"this (Qur'an) is surely a decisive Word,"
  86,14,"not a flippant jest.",footnotes:182668:1
  86,15,"They are devising a guile,",footnotes:182669:1
  86,16,"and I too am devising a guile.",footnotes:182670:1
  86,17,"So leave the unbelievers to themselves; respite them awhile.",footnotes:182671:1
